<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 5:20PM MST  by NWS Goodland</headline>
<description>A band of heavy snow is moving across northeast Colorado,
extending from Yuma to Burlington, moving northeast at around 50
mph.
Brief reductions in visibility to as low as a quarter of a mile
may occur with this band of snow.
Hazardous driving conditions associated with the visibility
reductions can be expected.</description>
